From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Benjamin Perseghetti <bperseghetti@rudislabs.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] qemu-native: fix statx libc syscall emulation

The statx syscall was using _syscall5 which bypasses pseudo's
interception when QEMU_LIBCSYSCALL=1 is set. This causes file
stat operations to fail incorrectly during chroot operations.

Convert sys_statx to use libc wrapper when do_libcsyscall is enabled.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [embedded specific]

Signed-off-by: Benjamin Perseghetti <bperseghetti@rudislabs.com>
---
 linux-user/syscall.c | 10 +++++++---
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/linux-user/syscall.c b/linux-user/syscall.c
index 05e8c6a..8acd8e0 100644
--- a/linux-user/syscall.c
+++ b/linux-user/syscall.c
@@ -453,8 +453,14 @@ _syscall5(int, kcmp, pid_t, pid1, pid_t, pid2, int, type,
  * It is assumed that struct statx is architecture independent.
  */
 #if defined(TARGET_NR_statx) && defined(__NR_statx)
-_syscall5(int, sys_statx, int, dirfd, const char *, pathname, int, flags,
-          unsigned int, mask, struct target_statx *, statxbuf)
+static int sys_statx(int dirfd, const char *pathname, int flags,
+                     unsigned int mask, struct target_statx *statxbuf)
+{
+    if (do_libcsyscall) {
+        return statx(dirfd, pathname, flags, mask, (struct statx *)statxbuf);
+    }
+    return syscall(__NR_statx, dirfd, pathname, flags, mask, statxbuf);
+}
 #endif
 #if defined(TARGET_NR_membarrier) && defined(__NR_membarrier)
 _syscall2(int, membarrier, int, cmd, int, flags)
